The ruling All Progressives Congress, APC has shifted its special convention earlier scheduled for 2pm today to 6pm. The shift in the time is because of the ongoing governorship and national assembly elections in Anambara, Edo, Imo and Zamfara States APC in a notice published on one of its official platforms said, “this is to inform all delegates expected at the APC National Convention on Saturday 6th October that the time has now been moved to 6pm. “This is to afford delegates from states that are just concluding their primaries, time to participate. “All delegates from outside Abuja are to get accredited at the  National Stadium while delegates within Abuja will be accredited at the old parade ground”, the notice read. 